{
  "stem": "7157.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So from zero to four years or three years of age, I was a-- I was a very rich-- a rich person.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my mother had a lot of gold and a lot of diamonds.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And later on, of course, this helped us in many, many ways.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But even then, at the beginning, we were able-- she was able to buy a horse and carriage and have a funeral.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My father was actually buried in a Jewish cemetery without a stone, without anything.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "This is like one day after the Hungarians moved in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "No markers, no Jewish markers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But he was buried properly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I remember we went to the-- there was a big issue whether kids should go to the funeral or not.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You know, in Europe, they were very funny in those days about rituals of that type.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But we did go to the funeral, George-- when I say we, I mean my brother and I.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And followed the wagons and actually we buried-- buried my father on that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was around May of 1941.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] as I recall-- just to tell you one thing about my father.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "There was only one time-- of course, this was 1941, so I was six years old.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "There's only one time that my father ever put a hand on me, so to say, in the six years.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He was a great, great, unbelievable personality person.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "A wonderful person.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I remember in Stanislawow he was-- somehow he found a bottle of ginger ale or soda water.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So he was giving George and me soda water.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I was complaining to him because he gave my brother a little more than me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I guess I started crying.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It was more than just complaining casually.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
